# Test and Build Planning

When creating todo lists or planning features that modify code, **always include validation steps:**

- Add `make test` (or `make test-backend` / `make test-frontend` for specific suites) as a validation step
- Add `make build` to verify the frontend builds successfully
- Include these steps in todo lists for features that modify code

This ensures tests and builds are validated as part of the workflow.

## Quick Reference

- **Build:** `make build` (frontend)
- **Tests:** `make test` (all), `make test-backend`, `make test-frontend`
- **Dev:** `make dev` (starts both servers)
- **Lint:** `make lint` (both), `make lint-backend`, `make lint-frontend`

See `AGENTS.md` for comprehensive project guidelines.
